description: From Middle English enserchen, from Old French encerchier. See search.

verbs.description: ensearch (third-person singular simple present ensearches, present participle ensearching, simple past and past participle ensearched)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, intransitive) To search; to try to find something.
(obsolete, transitive) To search for; to seek.
examples: by all the means you can to ensearch whether there is any meeting intended
